HEADWORD: Anteposition
<hw>An`te*po*si"tion</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. LL.
<ets>antepositio</ets>. See <er>Position</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Gram.)</fld>
<def>The placing of a before another, which, by ordinary rules, ought to
follow it.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

